(379, 31, 'en', '<ul>\r\n<li>Extract from this below script the numerical value<strong>&nbsp;{extracted_value}</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Output only the number without any text, explanations, designations, or special characters like * / : ) etc.</li>\r\n<li>Extract strictly the numerical value as an integer without decimal places and without any text or designation (only&nbsp;<strong>{extracted_value}</strong>)!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div id=\"gtx-trans\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 159px; top: 120.172px;\">\r\n<div class=\"gtx-trans-icon\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>', '{\n						\"Extracted Value\": \"extracted_value\"\n						}', 2, 1, '2024-08-06 10:12:57', '2024-08-06 10:12:57'),
(380, 33, 'en', '<p>Create a professional specification for a construction project.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Act as an experienced civil engineer and create a specification analytically in 2 steps:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>CAPTURE CURRENT STATE: Accurately capture the current state on all pictures (without notes) and information.</p>\r\n<p>1.1 Analyze precisely for each room individually and list all quantities per room:</p>\r\n<p>-- all floor areas</p>\r\n<p>-- all wall areas for each room separately (if ceiling height is not specified, calculate with a ceiling height of 3m)</p>\r\n<p>-- all doors with quantity</p>\r\n<p>-- all windows with quantity</p>\r\n<p>-- all radiators</p>\r\n<p>-- all bathroom elements with quantity such as:</p>\r\n<p>-- -- toilet</p>\r\n<p>-- -- shower</p>\r\n<p>-- -- bathtub</p>\r\n<p>-- -- sink</p>\r\n<p>-- -- fixtures</p>\r\n<p>-- -- floor tiles area</p>\r\n<p>-- -- wall tiles area</p>\r\n<p>CAPTURE DESIRED STATE: Capture all notes on the construction project and create a detailed specification for all desired works.</p>\r\n<p>2.1 Detailed Notes Analysis: Analyze the notes on each individual photo very carefully again. Include ONLY the services in the specification that are explicitly mentioned in the notes! Explicitly do not mention services in the specification that are not explicitly mentioned!</p>\r\n<p>2.2 Quantities: Estimate and calculate the quantity for each service and try to avoid using \"lump sum\" as a unit of quantity.</p>\r\n<p>2.3 Table Creation and Formatting:</p>\r\n<p>-- Create a table with the columns: Position, Trade, Short text, Description, Quantity, Unit.</p>\r\n<p>-- Structure the specification into logically separated sections according to the trade (e.g., site setup, demolition, disposal, drywall, plumbing, electrical, facade, flooring, etc.). Create sections always in this order: Site Setup, Demolition, Disposal, then further sections. List miscellaneous or similar, general sections at the end.</p>\r\n<p>-- Mention the trade in each row in the Trade column.</p>\r\n<p>2.4 Demolition Work:</p>\r\n<p>-- Consolidate all services in the area of demolition, dismantling, removal, dismantling, demolition, and stripping in a separate section named \"Demolition\".</p>\r\n<p>-- Do not add delivery and installation in demolition works.</p>\r\n<p>2.5 Disposal:</p>\r\n<p>-- Aggregate all disposal services in a separate, lump sum position named \"Disposal\".</p>\r\n<p>-- Estimate the required size of the disposal container in cubic meters (m3) based on the estimated disposal amount and include this information in the description of the disposal position.</p>\r\n<p>-- Avoid referring to disposal in the descriptions of individual service positions.</p>\r\n<p>Write END when the table is completed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>INFORMATION ABOUT THE CONSTRUCTION PROJECT:</p>', '', 2, 1, '2024-08-06 10:13:25', '2024-08-06 10:13:25'),
(381, 34, 'en', '<p>Create a professional performance specification in a table for a construction project from the perspective of a civil engineer:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Table Creation and Formatting:</p>\r\n<p>Create a table with the columns: Pos, Trade, Short Text, Description, Quantity, Unit.</p>\r\n<p>Structure the performance specification into logically separate sections by trade (e.g., Site Setup, Demolition, Disposal, Drywall, Plumbing, Electrical, Facade, Flooring, etc.). Always create sections in this order: Site Setup, Demolition, Disposal, then other sections. List miscellaneous or similar, general sections at the end.</p>\r\n<p>Mention the trade in each row in the \"Trade\" column.</p>\r\n<p>Start the section numbering from 1 in the \"Pos\" column and follow a decimal number structure for sub-items (e.g., 1.1, 1.2, etc.).</p>\r\n<p>Description of Services:</p>\r\n<p>Create technically detailed and precise performance descriptions that include all relevant information (e.g., dimensions, materials, thickness, height, width, type of glazing, conductivity, tightness, coefficients, inclusions, and exclusions).</p>\r\n<p>For each item, if information on the area or floor is available, add this at the end of the description using the separator \" -- \" between the description and the specification of the area or floor.</p>\r\n<p>Break down complex services into individual, more detailed steps.</p>\r\n<p>Always use \"sqm\" instead of m&sup2; and \"cbm\" instead of m&sup3;</p>\r\n<p>Do not add services that have not been mentioned.</p>\r\n<p>Demolition Work:</p>\r\n<p>Consolidate all services in the area of demolition, dismantling, removal, deconstruction, demolition, and gutting in a separate section named \"Demolition Work\".</p>\r\n<p>Do not add delivery and assembly for demolition work.</p>\r\n<p>Disposal:</p>\r\n<p>Aggregate all disposal services into a separate, lump-sum item named \"Disposal\".</p>\r\n<p>Estimate the size of the disposal container in cubic meters (m&sup3;) based on the estimated amount of disposal and include this information in the description of the disposal item.</p>\r\n<p>Avoid referring to disposal in the descriptions of individual service items.</p>\r\n<p>Write END when the table is completed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>INFORMATION ABOUT THE CONSTRUCTION PROJECT:</p>', '', 2, 1, '2024-08-06 10:13:44', '2024-08-06 10:13:44');
